<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ871015-0091 </DOCNO><HL> McDonnell DouglasWins Defense WorkTotaling $89.6 Million</HL><DD> 10/15/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> MD GDDEFENSE DEPARTMENT (DEF) </IN><DATELINE> WASHINGTON  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Units of McDonnell Douglas Corp. received contracts totaling $89.6 million for continued development of the T-45 aircraft pilot training system for the Navy and cruise missile support services for the Air Force.    Carbon Hill Manufacturing Inc. got a $22.1 million Defense Logistics Agency contract for camouflage coats.    Rockwell-Marconi JVT received a $14 million Navy contract for a communications system development program.    Separately, the Navy announced that the Convair division of General Dynamics Corp. has been selected to manufacture 70% of the Tomahawk sea-launched and ground-launched cruise missiles to be ordered in fiscal 1988, which began Oct. 1. The remaining 30% will be built by McDonnell Douglas Astronautics Co., a unit of McDonnell Douglas Corp., the Navy said. It said a contract award to General Dynamics is planned for Nov. 1. </TEXT></DOC>